{
  "texts": [
    "To validate the effectiveness of VERIFINER as a model-agnostic approach, we employ two groups of NER models as a test-bed for our evaluation: For fine-tuned models, we use ConNER (Jeong and Kang, 2023) and BioBERT (Lee et al., 2019), trained for the NER task on each dataset.",
    "For prompting-based LLMs, we consider GPT-NER (Wang et al., 2023a), which predicts entity spans of interest and their types in a generative manner via few-shot prompting.",
    "We compare VERIFINER with other methods that revise the initial prediction in a post-hoc manner.",
    "(1) Manual Mapping: Naive use of external knowledge to verify predictions.",
    "We reassign entity types by manually mapping semantic types found in the KB to the predefined labels."
  ]
}